[section#execpol.general
    [:en] In general
    [:zh_CN] 概述
]

[para]
[:en] This subclause describes classes that are [+execution policy] types.
[:zh_CN] 本子条款描述的类是[+执行策略]类型。

[:en] An object of an execution policy type indicates the kinds of parallelism
allowed in the execution of an algorithm and expresses the consequent
requirements on the element access functions.
[:zh_CN] 执行策略类型的对象，指定某个算法的执行中所允许的并行化种类，并体现了对
其所导致的元素访问函数的要求。

[begin:example]
[codeblock]
using namespace std;
vector<int> v = ...

// [:en] standard sequential sort
// [|:zh_CN] 标准的顺序性的排序
sort(v.begin(), v.end());

// [:en] explicitly sequential sort
// [|:zh_CN] 明确的顺序性的排序
sort(execution::seq, v.begin(), v.end());

// [:en] permitting parallel execution
// [|:zh_CN] 允许并行执行
sort(execution::par, v.begin(), v.end());

// [:en] permitting vectorization as well
// [|:zh_CN] 也允许进行向量化
sort(execution::par_unseq, v.begin(), v.end());
[codeblock:end]
[end:example]

[begin:note]
[:en] Because different parallel architectures may require idiosyncratic
parameters for efficient execution, implementations may provide additional
execution policies to those described in this standard as extensions.
[:zh_CN] 由于不同的并行架构对于高效的执行可能需要怪异的参数，实现可能会提供除了
本标准中所说明的执行策略之外的执行策略作为一种扩展。
[end:note]
